ng on hismy arm and laughing. \"You are a tease, doctor. I\'ve known a few of your type. Come along.\"\n\nHe\'s I\'m passionately fond of a mystery, because he I always hopes to solve it. So he I let himself myself be led by hismy companion, or, rather, by this unexpected plot.\n\nHe I omits the description of myher quarters. You can find one in several old, well-known French poets. One detail, however, missed by Regnier: two or three pictures of famous doctors hung on the walls.\n\nHow I she pampered himme! Big fire, mulled wine, cigars, and as Ishe offered these nice things, lighting a cigar for myselfherself, the clowning continued. \"Make yourself at home, my friend, get comfortable. Here you can remember the hospital and the good times of your youth. --What\'s this? Wherever did you get these grey hairs? You didn\'t have them not so long ago when you were L...\'s intern. I remember that you always assisted in his serious operations. Now there\'s a man who loves to cut and clip and amputate! You were the one who handed hsi his instruments, his sutures, his sponges.--And after the operation, how he\'d say, proudly looking at his watch, \'Five minutes, gentlemen!\'--Oh, I get to go everywhere. I really know these gentlemen.\"\n',NULL),(520,3,'bc06aa215b715e60:7207cc8a:10315bcd8ef:-7ec0','2005-04-06 01:12:36',861,'He',NULL),(521,3,'bc06aa215b715e60:7207cc8a:10315bcd8ef:-7ebf','2005-04-06 01:20:49',1611,'hsi',NULL),(522,2,'d5cd601c6178d124:6fdca5:1031714422e:-8000','2005-04-06 06:35:41',820,'I\'m passionately fond of a mystery, because I always hope to solve it. So I let myself be led by my companion, or, rather, by this unexpected plot.',NULL),(523,1,'d5cd601c6178d124:6fdca5:1031714422e:-7fff','2005-04-06 06:35:41',694,'I was very much concerned by her appearance and led on both by the urgency of her tone and a deep desire to be of assistance. ',NULL),(524,2,'d5cd601c6178d124:6fdca5:1031714422e:-7f30','2005-04-06 06:36:28',1358,'How she pampered me!',NULL),(525,1,'