ze together with the ribbons of her hat.\n\n\"No, I am not a doctor. Please let go!\" --\"Oh yes! You are a doctor. I can tell. Come along to my place. You\'ll like me, very much. Come on!...\" --\"No doubt, I\'ll come along later. After the doctor. Oh hell!...\" --\"Ah ha!\" she said, still hanging on my arm and laughing. \"You are a tease, doctor. I\'ve known a few of your type. Come along.\"\n\nI\'m passionately fond of a mystery, because I always hope to solve it. So I let myself be led by my companion, or, rather, by this unexpected plot.\n\nI omit the description of her quarters. You can find one in several old, well-known French poets. One detail, however, missed by Regnier: two or three pictures of famous doctors hung on the walls.\n\nHow she pampered me! Big fire, mulled wine, cigars, and as she offered these nice things, lighting a cigar for herself, the clowning continued. \"Make yourself at home, my friend, get comfortable. Here you can remember the hospital and the good times of your youth. --What\'s this? Wherever did you get these grey hairs? You didn\'t have them not so long ago when you were L...\'s intern. I remember that you always assisted in his serious operations. Now there\'s a man who loves to cut and clip and amputate! You were the one who handed hsi his instruments, his sutures, his sponges.--And after the operation, how he\'d say, proudly looking at his watch, \'Five minutes, gentlemen!\'--Oh, I get to go everywhere. I really know these gentlemen.\"\n',NULL),(1063,1,'d5cd601c6178d124:1aa7aac:10329b7494b:-7ebe','2005-04-09 21:40:16',1,'There WERE words here but I spilled my coffee.\n\n',NULL),(1064,5,'d5cd601c6178d124:1aa7aac:10329b7494b:-7e8e','2005-04-09 21:41:14',49,'coffee_stain.jpg',NULL),(1065,4,'d5cd601c6178d124:1aa7aac:10329b7494b:-7e8d','2005-04-09 21:47:27',0,'',NULL),(1066,3,'1ca04ceb76a170d5:1a9b4a4:10329d926ce:-7fff','2005-04-09 22:05:33',1590,'cut and clip and amputate',NULL),(1067,3,'1ca04ceb76a170d5:1a9b4a4:10329d926ce:-7ff8