fdab5fb60c8f4:-4e4edded:1037b6a549f:-7fff','2005-04-25 18:11:53',52,'.',NULL),(3008,4,'789e58e47fa03646:22c3e1a3:1037c6780cb:-7fd3','2005-04-25 22:55:54',0,'',NULL),(3009,3,'789e58e47fa03646:22c3e1a3:1037c6780cb:-7fd2','2005-04-25 23:02:01',1,'Blue has been praised for its nobility as the colour of life. But the true colour of life is not blue. Blue is the colour of violence, veins, or of life broken open, edited, and published. Or if blue is indeed the colour of life, it is so only on condition that it is not seen. Once fully visible, blue is the colour of life violated, and in the act of betrayal and of waste. Blue is the secret of life, and not the manifestation thereof. It is one of the things the value of which is secrecy, one of the talents that are to be hidden in a napkin. The true colour of life is the colour of the body, the colour of the covered blue, until it is broken open and becomes red, the implicit and not explicit blue of the living heart and the pulses. It is the modest colour of the unpublished blood',NULL),(3018,2,'acfafd8a453ecf6c:1081032:10367050c57:-7c01','2005-04-21 20:24:31',14,' to',NULL),(3032,2,'d6873a7da95bd015:33a222b5:101b6023128:-7fe3','2005-01-27 16:13:26',1330,'forward',NULL),(3033,1,'d6873a7da95bd015:33a222b5:101b6023128:-7fe2','2005-01-27 16:13:26',1321,'approving',NULL),(3034,1,'907576bcb6437d08:5c9ba9ad:101b6831fc6:-8000','2005-01-27 18:30:42',10,'(My host graciously led me up the stair\nand at the top he bid me stop and stare\nbehind a velvet curtain that he drew\naside for me alone to raptly view.)\n',NULL),(3035,1,'907576bcb6437d08:5c9ba9ad:101b6831fc6:-7e4f','2005-01-27 18:36:37',333,'(Here he proffered a rich and costly chair\nopposed to portrait more than passing fair;\nand certainly a wonder one might call, \nthat pleasing ornaments His Grace\'s hall,\nlovely as the Pyramids in sum,\na marvelous proper simulacrum.)\n',NULL),(3036,4,'907576bcb6437d08:5c9ba9ad:101b6831fc6:-7d32','2005-01-27 18:58:28',0,'A Copy of the Portrait of the Duchess',NULL),(3037,5,'907576bcb6437d08:5c9ba9ad:101b6831fc6:-7d30','2005-01-27 18:59:00',1357,'LadyDecies.jpg',NULL),(3038,1,'907576bcb6437d08:5c9ba9ad:101b6831fc6:-7d2f','2005-01-27 18:59:09',1,'My Liege,\n    Enclosed is a copy I have had executed in miniature of the Duke\'s wondrous portrait of his last Duchess, of which I spoke in my first report. Fra Pandolf, the painter, seems a gifted artisan in the modern mode; perhaps Your Grace might find commission for him to execute portraits of Your Grace or the Countess. As I mentioned, the Duke seems something of a jealous man, (felicitous as that will surely be in instructing Your Grace\'s young daughter in the proprieties and duties of matrimonial life) keeping his original hidden behind a velvet curtain in a hall alcove, and only assented to my having a copy made after repeated invocations of Your Grace\'s name, and reminders of the generous, nay, exorbitant, dowry that Your Grace represents. Even after finally relenting, he seemed quite grudging, and I would humbly advise Your Grace to relate to the Duke in any correspondence both your gratitude for his condescension and your intent to keep the copy nearly as cloistered as the original. Further letters and tokens of good will are forthcoming. As always, I remain\n                                                 Your Ob\'d\'t Serv\'t,\n                                                                      Silvio Quarante\n                                                                        Envoy Plenipotentiary\n\n                     ',NULL),(3041,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:8ebb5a:101b6b1ae2f:-8000','2005-01-27 19:21:32',1233,'hearty, spirited, and well-tended ',NULL),(3042,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7ffa','2005-01-27 19:54:05',2441,' Her mule rides also stopped.  The animal was dead soon after its mistress.  ',NULL),(3043,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7fba','2005-01-27 19:54:32',1310,'-- she would ride every day, with the mule breaking out into a lovely canter.  The lady was afraid of horses -- they were large, noisy and violent.  So insteads she was given the white mule -- it was gentle yet strong, and she lavished many caresses upon the dumb beast ',NULL),(3044,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7e2b','2005-01-27 19:56:47',1677,' and even the filthy Stableboy, who would watch her with pathetic devotion',NULL),(3045,2,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7da6','2005-01-27 19:57:45',2554,' ',NULL),(3064,4,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7bf3','2005-01-27 20:13:25',0,'A Sketch of My Lady\'s Mule',NULL),(3063,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7ba5','2005-01-27 20:14:42',1579,'.  An itinerant artist came by one day, and drew a picture of the mule for my lady -- a cheap, tawdry thing, not worth the time or homage she wasted upon it',NULL),(3062,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:a2d304:101b6cf42ac:-7bc4','2005-01-27 20:14:27',2674,'I ordered the foul picture burned.  ',NULL),(3051,1,'91de22f1aa05b4a6:3727fc29:101ba8dc59e:-7fff','2005-01-28 13:35:39',1624,' ',NULL),(3052,2,'91de22f1aa05b4a6:3727fc29:101ba8dc59e:-7f4b','2005-01-28 13:37:09',1623,' ',NULL),(3053,1,'91de22f1aa05b4a6:3727fc29:101ba8dc59e:-7f4a','2005-01-28 13:37:10',1547,' Honor should not surrender to love.  (Sure, my mother would beg to differ.)',NULL),(3055,3,'b1c9c29693f28dda:1404c51:101ba889b9c:-7ffa','2005-01-28 13:37:18',1321,'approvingforward ',NULL),(3057,2,'dd6d42e68f67f0f4:397443ed:101bad4a202:-7fd9','2005-01-28 14:43:11',2560,'a rarity',NULL),(3058,1,'dd6d42e68f67f0f4:397443ed:101bad4a202:-7fc5','2005-01-28 14:43:19',2541,'an unpopular piece.',NULL),(3059,1,'dd6d42e68f67f0f4:397443ed:101bad4a202:-7fb2','2005-01-28 14:43:44',2617,' I show it to you\nso that it might not go totally unnoticed. Sculpture is a peasant\'s \npleasure; a school for the colorblind.',NULL),(3060,2,'dd6d42e68f67f0f4:397443ed:101bad4a202:-7e6b','2005-01-28 14:53:05',114,'\n',NULL),(3061,1,'dd6d42e68f67f0f4:397443ed:101bad4a202:-7e6a','2005-01-28 14:53:06',9,'Though we be in a rush, we must stop and see a magnificent painting prominently displayed on yonder wall.',NULL),(3065,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:accd65:101bb5c37a3:-7eae','2005-01-28 17:37:02',33,'I don?t read, and I don?t write, and I don?t go into the villa ? no, signore!  What, me?  I care for the horses, and brush them, and clean their stalls, and I kept the lady?s mule.  A fine mule she was, signore -- tutto il mulo bianco -- all white and shining.  The lady liked the mule, and I kept the mule well, for I liked the lady.  The lady died, and the Duke said I must kill the mule.  Si, signore, I was sorry, for I liked the lady, and I liked the mule.  A man drew a picture of the mule and the lady kept it.  She showed it to me -- I saw it once.  Then the Duke said it must be burnt, but I stole it and kept it, for I liked the mule and I liked the lady.  Si, signore, you can see it, but do not tell anyone, for I am a poor boy and I must work.',NULL),(3076,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:13c765e:101bc2e395c:-7ffb','2005-01-28 21:24:20',886,'t slight scoliotic stoop ',NULL),(3075,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:13c765e:101bc2e395c:-7fec','2005-01-28 21:31:45',312,'The depth and passion of its earnest glance',NULL),(3074,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:13c765e:101bc2e395c:-7ffa','2005-01-28 21:24:20',1840,'?E\'en then would be some stooping, and I chuse\nNever to stoop',NULL),(3073,4,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7ffb','2005-01-29 15:44:55',0,'FQUna',NULL),(3078,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:13c765e:101bc2e395c:-7fed','2005-01-28 21:31:45',271,'all white and shining',NULL),(3079,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7ff3','2005-01-29 16:00:58',1229,'the white mule\nShe rode with',NULL),(3080,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7fec','2005-01-29 16:03:05',698,'Her mantle laps\nOver my Lady\'s wrist too much',NULL),(3082,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7ff4','2005-01-29 16:00:58',219,'a lowly Asse more white then snow,',NULL),(3083,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7fed','2005-01-29 16:03:05',309,'a vele, that wimpled was full low',NULL),(3084,1,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:178feba:101c02933ae:-7fe5','2005-01-29 16:04:30',1,'This description would appear to come from an imitator of the immortal poems of our Italian Ariosto and Tasso, mixing with the former\'s vigor the piety of the latter.\n\n',NULL),(3086,4,'9c9694cd2f312628:12fcdf5:101c1b1d310:-8000','2005-01-29 22:37:31',0,'Letter to the Duke',NULL),(3087,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:12fcdf5:101c1b1d310:-7fff','2005-01-29 22:37:39',748,'\n',NULL),(3088,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:12fcdf5:101c1b1d310:-7ffe','2005-01-29 22:37:40',760,'\n',NULL),(3089,1,'9c9694cd2f312628:12fcdf5:101c1b1d310:-7ffd','2005-01-29 22:37:44',33,'\n',NULL),(3092,1,'a21954c284be2a34:945b95:101c528505e:-7fdc','2005-01-30 14:59:36',2570,'\n\nSeems to me that my son, being a somewhat overspoiled only child, had more of a problem with jealousy than his duchess had with courting others.  She struck me as a genuinely amiable character.  I hoped for her to mother my grandchildren, but it is as though I\'ve lost all influence over my son.  ',NULL),(3094,4,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:74f160:101c61a7d90:-7ff7','2005-01-30 19:32:38',0,'For Sr Silvio: Confidential',NULL),(3095,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:74f160:101c61a7d90:-7ff2','2005-01-30 19:37:35',151,'Certain papers have been made public',NULL),(3096,3,'f0ed2a6d7fb07688:74f160:101c61a7d90:-7ff1','2005-01-30 19:37:35',1102,' Of the Duke\'s virility, fertility, and promise (but once rightly mated) of bountiful progeny, even now that the years of his youth lie behind him, no man need doubt.',NULL),(3098,1,'907576bcb6437d08:-235de05e:101c6baf6aa:-7f2c','2005-01-30 22:44:37',1355,'\n\nPost Script: Your Grace,\nRumors begin to circulate in a few circles that the good dottore\'s assessment is quite correct in regards to His Grace\'s ability to father children. I have little confirmation at the moment, and am unable to inquire of the Duke, for obvious reasons, but certain parties (some of questionable credibility) affirm that t