orize before one has data. Insensibly one begins to twist facts to suit theories, instead of theories to suit facts.\"',NULL),(3863,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fe3','2005-04-14 22:36:01',118,' \"It is a capital mistake to theorize before one has data. Insensibly one begins to twist facts to suit theories, instead of theories to suit facts.\"',NULL),(3864,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fec','2005-04-14 22:34:20',6070,'The analytical power should not be confounded with simple ingenuity; for while the analyst is necessarily ingenious, the ingenious man is often remarkably incapable of analysis.',NULL),(3865,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fe4','2005-04-14 22:36:01',6070,'The analytical power should not be confounded with simple ingenuity; for while the analyst is necessarily ingenious, the ingenious man is often remarkably incapable of analysis.',NULL),(3866,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fdf','2005-04-14 22:39:06',468,'Surely it is possibel to gather evidence without having a theory in mind. There are standard procedures based on previous cases that provide a good body of evidence from which theories can be formulated. Typical forms of primary evidence include eyewitness testimony, scrutiny of the crime scene if one should exist, and open observation and documentation of anything and everything in and proximal to the crime scene.',NULL),(3867,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7ffa','2005-04-14 22:25:07',265,'Nothing makes sense!!',NULL),(3868,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7ff0','2005-04-14 22:31:23',264,' Nothing makes sense!!',NULL),(3869,3,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fde','2005-04-14 22:39:06',861,'how I can get out of here',NULL),(3870,1,'a21954c284be2a34:15fa713:103439de5f4:-7fd8','2005-04-14 22:39:25',1193,'\n\nYoung Madame- \n\nI have attempted to provide you some sources to begin rummaging through.  Each seems to offer advice on how to analyze your situation.  I hope at least one will p