2For now we see through a glass, darkly; but then face to face: now I know in part; but then shall I know even as also I am known.',0),(2784,4,'','King James','                  \nJohn 8:12 Then spake Jesus again unto them, saying, I am the light of the world: he that followeth me shall not walk in darkness, but shall have the light of life. \nJohn 9:5 As long as I am in the world, I am the light of the world.',0),(2785,4,'','Darwin\'s tropics','       \nBrazil, in order to complete the chronometrical measurement of the world. We arrived there on August 1st, and stayed four days, during which I took several long walks. I was glad to find my enjoyment in tropical scenery had not decreased from the want of novelty, even in the slightest degree. The elements of the scenery are so simple that they are worth mentioning, as a proof on what trifling circumstances exquisite natural beauty depends.\nThe country may be described as a level plain of about three hundred feet in elevation, which in all parts has been worn into flat-bottomed valleys. This structure is remarkable in a granitic land, but is nearly universal in all those softer formations of which plains are usually composed. The whole surface is covered by various kinds of stately trees, interspersed with patches of cultivated ground, out of which houses, convents, and chapels arise. It must be remembered that within the tropics the wild luxuriance of nature is not lost even in the vicinity of large cities: for the natural vegetation of the hedges and hill-sides overpowers in picturesque effect the artificial labour of man. Hence, there are only a few spots where the bright red soil affords a strong contrast with the universal clothing of green. From the edges of the plain there are distant views either of the ocean, or of the great Bay with its low-wooded shores, and on which numerous boats and canoes show their white sails. Excepting from these points, the scene is extremely limited; following the level pathways, on each hand, only glimpses into the wooded valleys below can be obtained. The houses I may add, and especially the sacred edifices, are built in a peculiar and rather fantastic style of architecture. They are all whitewashed; so that when illumined by the brilliant sun of mid-day, and as seen against the pale blue sky of the horizon, they stand out more like shadows than real buildings.\n',0),(2786,4,'','King James','                  \nRevelation 1:7 Behold, he cometh with clouds; and every eye shall see him, and they also which pierced him: and all kindreds of the earth shall wail because of him. Even so, Amen. ',0),(2805,4,'','artifice','Can artifice, if it is recognized as artifice, explode into space?  And exactly why do you find it interesting Baudelaire? ',0),(2806,1,'fda8116d1c5f5e25:-66fbf36a:1035f19c9ff:-7ff7','To consider artifice',NULL,161),(2807,1,NULL,'To question Wilde on',NULL,161),(2808,1,NULL,'artifice vs. artific',NULL,161),(2809,1,'fda8116d1c5f5e25:-66fbf36a:1035f19c9ff:-7ff8','To consider artifice',NULL,1469),(2810,1,NULL,'artifice to artifici',NULL,161),(2811,4,'','Ether','What is he anethetized for?',0),(2812,4,'','Half','How can the streets be only half-deserted - is it the same as being half-crowded?',0),(2813,4,'','One night','If they\'re so cheap, why stay only for one night?',0),(2814,4,'','Time','Yikes.  There WILL always be time.  But now is only now, so time is fleeting, horrendously temporaral, as well as inescapable.  You know, one of those concepts that make your stomach contract when you realize you will be dead forever.  And ever.',0),(2815,4,'','Hesiod','Is this a reference to Hesiods myth of creation?',0),(2816,4,'','Coffee spoons','Coffee mugs work as well.  Except when they outnumber the days you actually have.',0),(2817,4,'','Porcelain','Porcelain dishes?  Or porcelain toilet?  ',0),(2818,4,'','Aura','There are psychological studies that suggest the \"aura\" one often sees before a severe migraine headache occassionally acc