\" What was formerly a tactic of resistance, \"You put the lime in the coconut, you drank them both up\" becomes the strategy of the Coca-Cola corporate deformance, \"You put the lime in the Coke you nut...\" Where once was resistance, now is complicity.\n\nIt is in this spirit that I offer here evidence that the deformers of ENNC982 were not the first ones to detect of whiff of processessed meat from Wilde\'s drama. Indeed, perhaps a little piece of new testament deformance has been with us, in the form of \"b-o-l-o-g-n-a\" (as the jingle would have it), all along...','2005-05-03 13:14:31','2005-05-03 13:23:29',NULL,20),(770,48,438,'Additions from the last move, highlighting the relationship between language and desire in Salome/Salami.','2005-05-04 11:44:51','2005-05-04 11:50:17',NULL,19),(771,48,426,'','2005-05-10 16:20:41',NULL,NULL,0),(772,46,376,'','2005-05-10 16:37:34',NULL,NULL,0),(773,47,387,'','2005-05-10 16:39:41',NULL,NULL,0),(775,54,456,'<html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  <body>\n    Breaking ground on this new game.\n\nAlthough with this particular example, i\'m beginning to wonder if Juxta Author \n    wouldn\'t be a better tool for comparison.\n\nWith a text like this, i do think it\'s interesting the way the digital history \n    can be traced through the glitches that speak to various errors in many \n    layers of reproduction. \n  </body>\n</html>\n','2004-10-15 17:36:06','2004-10-15 17:46:38',NULL,NULL),(776,55,445,'<html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  <body>\n    my first annotation\n  </body>\n</html>\n','2004-10-18 10:16:47','2004-10-18 10:17:10',NULL,NULL),(777,55,445,'<html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  <body>\n    define zymosis\n  </body>\n</html>\n','2004-10-18 10:25:33','2004-10-18 10:25:54',NULL,NULL),(786,55,449,'<html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  <body>\n  </body>\n</html>\n','2004-10-18 14:24:09','2004-10-18 14:31:46',NULL,NULL),(779,55,445,'<html>\n  <head>\n    \n  </head>\n  <body>\n    copy editing\n  </body>\n</html>\n','2